          2010-02-25 11:31:06 UTC
        </span>

      </div>




<pre class="bz_comment_text">What I think we need to do is to call &quot;setreuid(0,0)&quot; before doing the mtab locking. That'll block unprivileged users from sending signals to the program. root will still be able to send a signal to kill it though and users will still be able to hit ^c to break out of it.

I'll queue up a patch to do that in the setuid patchset I'm working on.
</pre>
    </div>

